    "content": "**Geopolitiks Snacks** - May 7, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 🌊 Hormuz diplomacy became a military status toggle\n\nWashington is trying to sell pause, pressure and peace as the same sentence. The strait is not helping.\n\n- **The whiplash:** AP says U.S. messaging jumped from escorting stranded ships, to calling the operation concluded, to Trump pausing it for talks.\n- **The threat:** Trump then warned bombing could resume if Tehran rejects U.S. terms for reopening the Strait of Hormuz.\n- **The contradiction:** officials still describe the ceasefire as alive, despite Iranian missiles and drones, U.S. fire on Iranian assets and oil still flowing through a panic premium.\n\n*The ceasefire has become Schrödinger's policy: active, paused and escalating until observed by cable news.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP](https://apnews.com/article/trump-iran-war-confusion-messaging-contradiction-20471bb90ad7abd6381a761fffeb8e96) | [AP](https://apnews.com/article/b70f88f5aeef24e3c3e139c52f79c6fe)\n\n---\n\n## 🕊️ Russia ignored Kyiv's ceasefire before its own parade truce\n\nMoscow has discovered a neat diplomatic product: reject the ceasefire you dislike, advertise the one around your parade.\n\n- **The attacks:** AP says Russia fired dozens of drones after Ukraine's unilateral ceasefire began at midnight Wednesday.\n- **The toll:** Ukrainian officials said Russian strikes on Tuesday killed 27 civilians and wounded 120; the UN counted at least 70 civilians killed since Friday.\n- **The split:** Russia still says it will pause fighting for May 8-9 around Victory Day, while Kyiv says violations will trigger response.\n\n*Holiday truces work better when they are not preceded by air alerts.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP](https://apnews.com/article/russia-ukraine-war-ceasefire-drones-missiles-crimea-484f28530eb0c2ce64fff9be5eb7c9d3) | [Reuters via Investing.com](https://www.investing.com/news/world-news/ukraine-says-russia-violated-ceasefire-initiated-by-kyiv-4661789)\n\n---\n\n## 🗻 Pakistan marked the Kashmir anniversary with a fresh warning label\n\nThe subcontinent remains committed to commemorating crisis by reminding everyone how quickly it could stop being commemoration.\n\n- **The warning:** Pakistan's military said any hostile design would be met with greater strength, precision and resolve than India saw in May 2025.\n- **The memory:** last year's four-day conflict began after a Kashmir attack killed 26 people, most of them Hindu tourists, and led to reciprocal strikes.\n- **The brake:** AP notes dozens died before a U.S.-brokered ceasefire halted the fighting on May 10.\n\n*One year later, the ceasefire is still doing the diplomatic equivalent of holding a glass table together with tape.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP](https://apnews.com/article/pakistan-india-war-kashmir-anniversary-683ab7446c2f019f545d68ddd3e1a7f1)\n"
  }
]
